    "long_instructions": "A researcher is analyzing real estate trends in Connecticut to compare the number of homes sold of a given type (single family, condo, etc.).\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">RealEstate.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">countMatching()</code> method. It should return 1 if the given home has the same <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">type</code> as the parameter and the name of the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">town</code> is longer than 4 characters. Otherwise, return 0.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">countMatching()</code> method on 5 different <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Home</code> objects and pass the total into <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResult()</code>.\r\n",
